Giant Vendetta				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Story																															PRETEXT:Prerequisite:You must have been knocked unconscious in an encounter with a challenging giant foe or have a regional background trait tied to giants.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.13
CATEGORY=FEAT|Giant Vendetta.MOD																																																																					DESC:[Not Implemented] Your life has been shaped by an encounter with giants.
CATEGORY=FEAT|Giant Vendetta.MOD																																																																																																										BENEFIT:Choose one kind of giant (such as hill or stone); you must choose a kind of giant that allows you to qualify for this feat. You gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls against giants of that kind. You also gain a + 1 bonus on Knowledge (local) checks regarding giants of thai kind and can attempt those Knowledge checks untrained. In addition, you gain a + 1 dodge bonus to AC against all giants. Goal: Defeat a giant of the chosen kind that is a challenging foe. Completion Benefit: You gain a +1 bonus on initiative checks when facing a giant of any kind, which increases to +2 against giants of the selected kind. Whenever you defeat a giant of any kind that is a challenging foe, the benefits of this feat that apply only to a specific kind of giant now also apply to giants of the kind you defeated.
